;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;As an example,=\r\n someone I know does homam everyday and is a regular and rational person wi=\r\nthout an imaginative/intuitive mind that gets visions, dreams etc.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;br&gt;Though his sadhana was saattwik (even his visualization of fierce deit=\r\nies was in Upanishadic terms), oneday he felt a strong urge to mix blood in=\r\n rice and offer it in homam. It did not seem natural to him and so he did n=\r\not act on that instinct though it re-appeared in his mind several times tha=\r\nt\n day. He ignored it as an unnatural thought for him.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;A coupl=\r\ne of days later, he received a mail from someone close to him but living 10=\r\n00s of miles away. This person happened to go to a smashan that weekend nig=\r\nht for meditation and saw some Tantriks doing a\n &quot;Rakta Chamunda&quot; homam. Th=\r\ney were offering ingredients dipped in their blood in homam. He just sat th=\r\nere and observed them. He later sent a mail about it.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;When the=\r\n original person received the mail, he realized why he had that thought a c=\r\nouple of days back. His mind was simply resonating to the thoughts of the o=\r\nther person, without a complete awareness. In fact, such a thing happened t=\r\no him several times with the same person.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;There were also many=\r\n occasions when he would randomly talk about some topic and one specific pe=\r\nrson in the room would claim that that person was thinking about exactly th=\r\nat topic. Again, the question in the mind of that person resonated in the o=\r\nther mind and the person started talking about it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=\r\n=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_57&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=3D=\r\n&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_58 yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2554_1=\r\n373624150759_58\n yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2741_1373624150759_59 yiv9980592182=\r\nyui_3_7_2_3201_1373624150759_60&quot; id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_13736241=\r\n50759_59&quot; style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13px; font-family: arial=\r\n, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-style: =\r\nnormal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1=\r\n373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;=\r\nFirst, how does this work? Simple - resonance between minds.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;S=\r\nuppose you are talking loud. You may not hear what others around you are sa=\r\nying. Similarly, if your mind is vibrating with too many thoughts, it may n=\r\not resonate to the vibrations in other minds around it.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span\n id=3D&quot;yiv=\r\n9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;But, if you are relatively calm,=\r\n you can hear what others are saying. Similarly, if your mind is relatively=\r\n calm, it may pick up vibrations in other minds around it (or even 1000s of=\r\n miles away if there is some attachment/connection) and resonate to those v=\r\nibrations!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_20=\r\n26_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_137362=\r\n4150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;=\r\nyiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Second, how to know where the thought is comin=\r\ng from?&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;When an infant listens to tens of voices, he simply he=\r\nars different sounds and does not know from which face each sound is coming=\r\n from. Over time, after many observations and correlations, brain learns to=\r\n discern from which face each sound is coming from. Later, one may\n recogni=\r\nze a voice even when the face is behind a curtain or otherwise invisible!&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Similarly, if one so wishes, one can develop the ability to dis=\r\ncern the source of each thought that vibrates the mind, after much observat=\r\nion and correlation. The mind can of course be trained. However, a seeker o=\r\nf self-realization need not actively pursue such an ability, for it serves =\r\nno useful purpose in Self-realization.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9=\r\n980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182=\r\nyui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv998=\r\n0592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_=\r\n2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;The ability to \ncalm the vibrations in the mind due =\r\nto conditioning and then the ability\n to calm any vibrations due to resonan=\r\nce is more important than the \nability to discern the source of vibrations.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_=\r\n68&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Whether a thought that vibrates one&#39;s mind right now is coming f=\r\nrom one&#39;s own conditioning or sensory observation or someone else&#39;s, is not=\r\n the crux. The crux is knowing whether one should perform any physical/ment=\r\nal *action* based on thought, to fulfill one&#39;s swa-dharma, or just observe =\r\nthe thought and leave it (move on). A true seeker&#39;s focus will be on that a=\r\nbility, i.e. developing clarity regarding one&#39;s own dharma, than figuring o=\r\nut the source of each thought. The latter can be a distraction or even an e=\r\ngo trap.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Nevertheless, Nature may sometimes give one abilities=\r\n that one does not actively pursue or need (perhaps because one desired it =\r\nlong back). A true seeker neither tries for nor resists what is not needed =\r\nby one. One does not dwell on it in either case and moves on.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span\n id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;=\r\nspan id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_13=\r\n73624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;O=\r\nne may argue that certain &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_13=\r\n73624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;s=\r\npecial &lt;/span&gt;abilities can help one pay off karmik debts on one&#39;s way to l=\r\niberation. However, one can (must) trust Nature to arrange for circumstance=\r\ns to pay off one&#39;s debts. The key is to be aware of what one can give other=\r\ns in any given circumstance and give it without holding back. If one gets u=\r\nsed to giving without expecting any payback, Nature will automatically arra=\r\nnge for all of one&#39;s debts to be paid off. No special abilities are needed.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Of course, when there is a clash between giving thing X to pe=\r\nrson A vs giving\n thing Y to person B, one needs to use one&#39;s discretion. T=\r\nhat is where our conditioning may block us from the right call. As we know =\r\nour dharma better and get a sense of which of our dharmas are higher, we ma=\r\ny start to make the right calls.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;The bottomline: Try to know y=\r\nour dharma (declared by the spark of divinity in heart). Try to follow it t=\r\no the best of ability. Give whatever you can give others, without expecting=\r\n any payback. Ignore thoughts arising in mind, which do not contribute to f=\r\nulfillment of your dharma, no matter what the source of that thought may be=\r\n.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759=\r\n_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;spa=\r\nn id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_13736=\r\n24150759_68&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Befo=\r\nre I sign off, a\n couple of words on Rakta Chamunda from the story above.&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_137362415=\r\n0759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=3D&quot;yiv9980592182yui_3_7_2_2026_1373624150759_68&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Th=\r\ne verb cham means to \ndrink/eat/consume. The verb mund means to shave or de=\r\nplete. Chamunda \nmeans one who drinks and finishes. Rakta means conditionin=\r\ng or coloring \n(the words rakti (attachment) and virakti (detachment) come =\r\nfrom the \nsame root). Rakta Chamunda is the one who drinks and empties all =\r\n\nconditioning that causes desires. Offering blood is an approximation. Also=\r\n, ironic that some people worship Rakta Chamunda for vashikaran..&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrolog=\r\ny &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.Vedi